tion to unseen domains (e.g., medical vs. legal), and assess real-time adaptability in simulated live evaluation environments. Ideal outcomes include achieving >0.80 average Spearman correlation across all dimensions, demonstrating measurable improvement after counterfactual feedback loops, and outperforming baselines in identifying subtle coherence failures. We will release CogEval-Graph code, pre-trained adapters, and the CogBench dataset.",
